	<text>
		<body>
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001077_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1'--> 
<!--Hand 01 16247 top left--><!-- Hand 02 69 top left--><!--Hand 03 91798 top right-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Hadley Green</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">20<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> August</p>
<lb/><p rend="right"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>1857</p>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">My Dear Sir</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>I have been 
<lb/>quite unable to 
<lb/>look over your 
<lb/>very kind 
<w>inves-<lb break="no"/>tigation</w> of <term type="reference">my 
<lb/>work</term> as I am 
<lb/>striving to have 
<lb/>the correction 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001077_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>of the press all 
<lb/>over by the 
<lb/>25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> to go to 
<lb/>Dublin meeting 
<lb/>of the association<!--can I have this??--></p>
<lb/><p>As you seem 
<lb/>to have great 
<lb/>facility for 
<lb/>this work I 
<lb/>have been wishing 
<lb/>to screw up my 
<lb/>courage so far as 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001077_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>to ask you (if 
<lb/>it is not a piece 
<lb/>of outrageous 
<lb/>indulgence) to 
<lb/>ask you edit 
<lb/>them. <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r </hi> Maclear</persName>
<lb/>said to the <choice><abbr>R.G.S.</abbr><expan>Royal Geographical Society</expan></choice><!--Chris wants a note on RGS - do we un abbr it and then term type="note" ??-->
<lb/>some public body 
<lb/>ought to print 
<lb/>them. <persName>Sir Roderick</persName>
<lb/>said looking towards 
<lb/>me "we shall 
<lb/>be happy to do it" 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001077_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/><!-- Hand 03 91798 top right-->Now I dont know 
<lb/>whether <persName>Murray</persName>
<lb/>would think it 
<lb/>an encumbrance 
<lb/>or not to <term type="reference">my own 
<lb/>book</term>. I believe 
<lb/><persName>Arrowsmith</persName> would 
<lb/>like some of them 
<lb/>suppressed. but 
<lb/>I dont like any 
<w>-<lb break="no"/>thing</w> like "cooking" 
<lb/>On that account 
<lb/>I <del type="strikethrough">never</del> sent <term type="reference">my 
<lb/>observation book</term>
<lb/><!-- Hand 04 Sotheby - 12-12-22 bottom left-->

	<pb n="0005" facs="liv_001077_0005"/><!--pb/@n='5'--> 
<!--Hand 02 69 top left--><!--Hand 03 91798 top right-->to the Royal Observatory 
<lb/>but never have 
<lb/>had time to look 
<lb/>at their work 
<lb/>If you had <choice><sic>leizure </sic><corr>leisure</corr></choice>
<lb/>and inclination 
<lb/>to examine the 
<lb/>whole with 
<lb/>the observation 
<lb/>book too &amp; 
<lb/>give your opinion 
<lb/>and make any 
<lb/><!-- Hand 04 Sotheby's 12.12.22 -->

	<pb n="0006" facs="liv_001077_0006"/><!--pb/@n='6'--> 
additional remarks 
<lb/>you please. I 
<lb/>should feel it 
<lb/>a great favour 
<lb/>It might possibly 
<lb/>not suit <persName>Murray</persName>
<lb/>as the boards 
<lb/>of <term type="reference">my book</term> are 
<lb/>ready. but 
<lb/>then it would 
<lb/>be in the Journal 
<lb/>of the <choice><abbr>R.G.S.</abbr><expan>Royal Geographical Society</expan></choice>

	<pb n="0007" facs="liv_001077_0007"/><!--pb/@n='7'--> 
<lb/>and I could 
<lb/>put a note into 
<lb/>mine referring 
<lb/>to the observations 
<lb/>Edited by <persName><choice><abbr>Capt<hi rend="sup">n</hi></abbr><expan>Captain</expan></choice>
<lb/>Toynbee</persName>.</p>
<lb/><p>If however 
<lb/>this is inconvenient 
<lb/>please dont 
<lb/>refer to it and 
<lb/>excuse your 
<lb/>much obliged</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">D. Livingstone</p>

	<pb n="0008" facs="liv_001077_0008"/><!--pb/@n='8'-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><!-- Hand 05 91798 top right-->I would ask 
<lb/><persName>Murray</persName> if you 
<lb/>can spare the 
<lb/>time. I <del type="strikethrough">would</del> shall 
<lb/>send a rough 
<lb/>copy of <persName>Arrow
<lb/>Smiths</persName> map as 
<lb/>soon as I know 
<lb/>your mind</p>
<lb/>
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Captain Toynbee</persName></p>
			
</div>
